<paragraph blockId="26.[264,1325,284,1870]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
Etymology. The species name refers to the 
<collectingCountry box="[838,915,1644,1670]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">ALAS</collectingCountry>
transect at ca. 
<quantity box="[1101,1193,1644,1670]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0699999999999998" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" unit="m" value="1070.0">1070 m</quantity>
where the 
<typeStatus box="[264,366,1684,1710]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">holotype</typeStatus>
was collected. 
<collectingCountry box="[556,633,1684,1710]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">ALAS</collectingCountry>
is the acronym of the NSF­funded project known as the Arthropods of La Selva.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[264,1325,284,1870]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
Remarks. The association of the sexes is equivocal since females were collected a considerable distance form the 
<typeStatus box="[599,649,1804,1830]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">type</typeStatus>
locality, and is based primarily on forewing length and pattern.
</paragraph>
